Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.16,0:00:02.63,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}My name's Conan Edogawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.63,0:00:05.73,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}High school student Shin'ichi was\Nforced to take a drug that shrunk him!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.73,0:00:08.46,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Although smaller, my mind remains\Nthat of a sharp detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.46,0:00:10.37,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Today's "MuneDoki" is the last one!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.37,0:00:13.54,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The alibi's just too strong!\NLet your heart beat to the case!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.54,0:00:15.47,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's always only one truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.75,0:01:44.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow! Look how fancy it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.49,0:01:46.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now I see why it's a five-star hotel!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.82,0:01:48.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is going to be great, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.57,0:01:50.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.16,0:01:54.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You kids are way too spoiled...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.13,0:01:57.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're only here because the restaurant's on the way, got that!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.43,0:01:59.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, we know!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.70,0:02:05.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, isn't that the lawyer who wants to hire you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.14,0:02:09.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yep, that's him! Mr. Tatsumi!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.45,0:02:09.42,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Sohei Tatsumi (48)\N—Attorney—
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.18,0:02:13.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your great detective work is highly admired,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.05,0:02:16.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,even within our judicial circles!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.29,0:02:20.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, my work doesn't begin to compare to yours...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.06,0:02:24.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All of my groups know about you too! It's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.63,0:02:30.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Having your office in this posh hotel is really impressive!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.77,0:02:37.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tricks like this are necessary when dealing with corporations.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.51,0:02:42.30,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So he's a popular lawyer who advises a number of large corporations...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.38,0:02:49.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.36,0:02:54.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What would you like to drink?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.16,0:02:56.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll have coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.03,0:02:58.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These two don't need anything; I'll kick them out soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.93,0:03:02.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no need to hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.27,0:03:05.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take your time and relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.04,0:03:07.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hello? Room service, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.27,0:03:11.94,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If there's no reason to hurry,\Nthen why's he so fixated on the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.94,0:03:14.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me while I use the restroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.52,0:03:25.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, but could someone answer that for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.59,0:03:33.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It automatically records calls!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.53,0:03:35.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.47,0:03:37.43,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Oh? You're not my husband...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.43,0:03:39.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Um, who may I ask is calling?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.97,0:03:44.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who do you think? Mrs. Tatsumi, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.64,0:03:47.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oops.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.41,0:03:48.95,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.95,0:03:50.01,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Little boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.01,0:03:51.67,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Could you put my husband on?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.67,0:03:55.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, just a minute—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.15,0:03:57.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Lawyer, it's your wife...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.86,0:04:00.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She never learns...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.66,0:04:02.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's me. I have guests right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.93,0:04:04.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can talk later.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.60,0:04:09.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry. Now, about my job.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.37,0:04:11.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before that... Ran, Conan.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.48,0:04:13.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.00,0:04:14.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's go, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.94,0:04:17.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a tea lounge in the lobby.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.61,0:04:21.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tell them my room number\Nand order whatever you'd like.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.68,0:04:23.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.82,0:04:29.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd like you to investigate possible infidelity.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.32,0:04:31.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of my wife, Kazumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.56,0:04:40.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's almost been an hour...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.20,0:04:42.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here he comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.40,0:04:43.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.50,0:04:45.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, there you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.57,0:04:48.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That took long. Is it a hard job?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.44,0:04:50.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, not exactly...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.24,0:04:52.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.44,0:04:57.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He just wouldn't stop babbling\Nabout how he'd like
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.58,0:05:02.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to trust his wife again,\Nso it took longer than I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.55,0:05:06.42,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So he's investigating the wife's infidelity...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.42,0:05:08.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I took the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.66,0:05:11.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So let's go eat at this restaurant of yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.50,0:05:12.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurray!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.93,0:05:17.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which is what I'd like to say,\Nbut this is the underground parking garage!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.37,0:05:18.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The restaurant is up there!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.99,0:05:19.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whoops...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.44,0:05:22.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were you even being serious about going?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.88,0:05:26.28,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Mr. Tatsumi...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.28,0:05:27.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan! Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.50,0:05:28.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.89,0:05:36.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think I drank too much...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.56,0:05:42.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A police car. I wonder what for?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.73,0:05:45.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a huge mansion!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.03,0:05:47.13,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So this is Mr. Tatsumi's house...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.73,0:05:51.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lawyers must really make a lot...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.64,0:05:54.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Megure. I brought Detective Mouri.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.64,0:05:57.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! Thanks for coming, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.57,0:06:00.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the deal, Inspector?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.25,0:06:05.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, come have a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.25,0:06:09.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You two wait there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.20,0:06:20.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that's Mr. Tatsumi's wife?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.40,0:06:23.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. Kazumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. 27 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.17,0:06:27.17,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Tatsumi Kazumi (27)\N—Wife of Mr. Tatsumi—
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.17,0:06:26.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cause of death was suffocation by strangulation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.00,0:06:28.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no question this was a murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.11,0:06:33.88,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A staple!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.88,0:06:35.35,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What's this doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.35,0:06:37.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Alright, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.88,0:06:40.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you think you're doin'?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.02,0:06:42.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, now, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.05,0:06:46.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All three of your testimonies are needed this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.06,0:06:47.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Testimonies?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.29,0:06:50.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's true that my wife and I didn't get along.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.79,0:06:57.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I hired Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to check up on her...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.40,0:07:00.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector. What was the estimated time of death?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.90,0:07:03.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We won't know the details until the autopsy,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.84,0:07:09.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but judging from the state of rigor mortis,\NI'd say between 2:00 and 3:00 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.31,0:07:10.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's when we were—
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.91,0:07:13.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's when we were at the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.58,0:07:14.72,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Now I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.72,0:07:18.39,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So they called us here to confirm his alibi...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.39,0:07:22.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I parted with Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and left the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.26,0:07:27.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I finished researching my next case,\Nand then when I came home, my wife was—
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.43,0:07:28.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,—as you saw...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.83,0:07:33.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}. You're certain you were with Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.60,0:07:35.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,between 2:00 and 3:00?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.21,0:07:37.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. I'm certain.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.44,0:07:41.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He only disappeared from my sight once,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.95,0:07:44.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and that was for only a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.01,0:07:47.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh yes, the phone rang then...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.48,0:07:50.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah! Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} answered it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.39,0:07:54.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah! They said, "I'm Mrs. Tatsumi, of course!"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.49,0:07:58.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means she was still alive at that time?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.56,0:08:02.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The tape of that conversation should still be in the phone at the hotel!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.57,0:08:06.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?! May we borrow this tape?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.44,0:08:08.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course. That's fine with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.91,0:08:11.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At any rate, Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} was with me
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.48,0:08:16.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,between 2:00 and 3:00—his alibi is airtight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.05,0:08:21.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And besides, the hotel is 10 kilometers from his home.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.59,0:08:26.58,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,"Lawyer's Wife Murdered"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.99,0:08:29.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Lawyer's wife murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.46,0:08:33.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The focus of the investigation is on the victim's associate?"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.86,0:08:36.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was having an affair.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.87,0:08:41.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Tatsumi's wife was killed by her other lover?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.07,0:08:44.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Judging from the scene of the crime,\Nit wasn't a robbery.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.54,0:08:48.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our testimonies cleared Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} of all suspicion.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.55,0:08:51.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which narrows it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.11,0:08:56.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it! I lost that case thanks to whoever killed her!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.22,0:08:58.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That makes me mad!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.69,0:08:59.96,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Something's not right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.96,0:09:03.06,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There are too many things about this case that bother me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.06,0:09:08.77,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Why was it necessary to put the body in the bathtub?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.77,0:09:11.30,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What was that staple for?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.30,0:09:16.07,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The way Mr. Tatsumi stalled the old man for an hour...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.07,0:09:18.84,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Why was he so fixated on the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.84,0:09:23.15,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Was it mere coincidence that he had someone else pick up the phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.15,0:09:26.12,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What did he put in the car trunk?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.12,0:09:29.95,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I guess all the questions start from the hotel!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.59,0:09:34.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was that Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.19,0:09:35.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}! Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.96,0:09:38.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll be back in time!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.46,0:09:42.97,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This is Mr. Tatsumi's office.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.97,0:09:45.74,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The guest elevator is down there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.74,0:09:49.11,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Similarly, the employee elevator is over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.11,0:09:51.13,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The emergency exit is far, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.31,0:09:57.64,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.39,0:10:06.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a laundry chute...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.84,0:10:22.81,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The staple!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.81,0:10:24.00,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.58,0:10:29.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As always,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.01,0:10:33.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've prepared the room next to my office,\Nso please make yourselves at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.35,0:10:36.34,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The room next to his office? As always?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.95,0:10:39.66,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This is—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.66,0:10:42.79,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Where is it coming from?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.79,0:10:43.85,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}From here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.30,0:10:52.20,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So that's what this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.20,0:10:55.44,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}They have a music box instead of an alarm clock buzzer!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.44,0:10:58.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you staying here, little boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.38,0:11:00.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I'm exploring!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.49,0:11:02.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or are you getting into trouble?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.08,0:11:06.48,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That reminds me—
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.45,0:11:12.46,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}—the music box stopped during the phone call!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.46,0:11:14.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a rare alarm clock!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.79,0:11:16.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do any other rooms have one?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.99,0:11:19.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course. All the rooms do.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.86,0:11:23.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They each have a real music box\Nhooked up to a timer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.97,0:11:26.10,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I've finally found it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.10,0:11:29.83,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Definitive proof that Mr. Tatsumi killed her!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.74,0:11:36.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're late!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.25,0:11:37.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look how late you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.98,0:11:40.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You knew we were going somewhere!\NWhere were you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.92,0:11:43.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where's the old man?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.02,0:11:45.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He already left!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.20,0:11:57.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You did this! You killed Kazumi!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.70,0:12:00.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm with the police. What's going on here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.94,0:12:02.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.51,0:12:06.43,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Shunzo Hirose (30)\NDesign Engineer
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.61,0:12:06.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hirose. I'm a design engineer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.08,0:12:09.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm the man you're looking for.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.41,0:12:11.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had an affair with Kazumi, the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.58,0:12:12.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.02,0:12:19.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I didn't kill her! Why would I?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.39,0:12:22.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was about to divorce this guy
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.06,0:12:24.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and marry me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.83,0:12:26.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's news to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.85,0:12:28.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't play dumb!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.63,0:12:30.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You knew!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.97,0:12:32.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He knew?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.90,0:12:40.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Assuming I had known, why would I kill her?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.48,0:12:45.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As a lawyer, I've heard about scores of cases
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.58,0:12:49.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,in which affairs led to murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.09,0:12:50.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.09,0:12:52.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And besides, I have an alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.69,0:12:55.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't possibly have killed her.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.79,0:12:57.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.93,0:12:59.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I can vouch for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.67,0:13:03.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hirose{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.50,0:13:06.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So how about yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.24,0:13:08.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's your alibi?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.67,0:13:11.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where were you between 2:00 and 3:00 PM
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.37,0:13:13.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,on the day she was killed?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.31,0:13:15.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.21,0:13:21.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where were you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.69,0:13:24.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was tricked!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.06,0:13:25.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tricked?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.72,0:13:28.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I came here because of Kazumi's letter...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.96,0:13:30.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.56,0:13:37.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I'll be waiting for you at home at 2:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.30,0:13:38.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Signed, Kazumi."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.90,0:13:40.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But she wasn't home.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.70,0:13:45.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I rang the doorbell,\Nbut nobody answered, so I left!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.34,0:13:47.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is really hard to believe,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.34,0:13:50.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,since you were at the scene when it happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.58,0:13:54.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyone can easily make something like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.52,0:13:56.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're a sore loser!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.59,0:13:59.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's clear that you're the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.49,0:14:01.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector. Take him in.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.26,0:14:03.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He ruined my case!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.58,0:14:04.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ruined?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.26,0:14:06.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You got it all wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.16,0:14:07.93,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He always does!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.93,0:14:11.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hirose{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. I'd like you\Nto come down to the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.80,0:14:13.46,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Sorry, old man!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.48,0:14:20.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.61,0:14:22.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm fine, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.75,0:14:24.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No! It wasn't me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.48,0:14:27.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.15,0:14:34.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The real sore loser isn't Hirose{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}—\Nit's you, Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.79,0:14:36.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.96,0:14:39.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you saying Mr. Tatsumi is the killer?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.50,0:14:41.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Precisely.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.90,0:14:47.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really now, this is absurd.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.90,0:14:51.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This will tarnish your name\Nas a great detective, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.41,0:14:57.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I could say the exact same thing to you, Mr. Tatsumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.25,0:15:02.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It truly was an impressive trick of utilizing blind spots.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.25,0:15:04.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You had me completely fooled.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.35,0:15:06.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The place a body is found doesn't necessarily equate
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.82,0:15:08.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to the location of the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.93,0:15:12.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, the murder didn't take place here at your home,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.60,0:15:16.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but at the hotel!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.03,0:15:17.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.03,0:15:19.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.84,0:15:20.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.74,0:15:25.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The voice on the tape of the phone call with Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.04,0:15:30.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,was professionally analyzed and determined to be the victim's!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.05,0:15:32.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, of course it was her.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.65,0:15:37.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because she called from the room next to Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}'s office,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.22,0:15:39.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,which he had rented.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.96,0:15:41.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.07,0:15:42.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The room next door?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.46,0:15:45.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On that day, Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.46,0:15:51.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,made his wife wait in the guest room\Nthat he always uses for clients.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.43,0:15:55.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He then had her call the hotel at a predetermined time
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.64,0:15:58.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,with a cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.01,0:16:02.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He made someone else answer the unconnected call.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.75,0:16:04.35,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.35,0:16:09.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because nobody would ever suspect that the caller was in the very next room.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.92,0:16:13.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Immediately after his business with me ended,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.92,0:16:17.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he went next door and killed his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.93,0:16:21.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He put the body in a laundry basket
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.50,0:16:27.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and dropped it down a nearby laundry chute.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.87,0:16:31.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was the hotel employees' break time
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.37,0:16:37.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so there wasn't a soul to be found,\Nwas there, Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.31,0:16:42.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, the bag with the body was stapled.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.32,0:16:45.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stapled with a cleaning tag.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.46,0:16:49.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was the staple found in the bathroom, Inspector Megure.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.69,0:16:51.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.76,0:16:54.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why was the body in the bathtub?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.23,0:16:56.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His plan probably started when he realized
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.53,0:17:03.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that the trunk and the bathtub are about the same size.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.01,0:17:05.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The body would stiffen,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.24,0:17:09.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so he couldn't just toss it in the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.08,0:17:15.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then he pointed the finger at Hirose{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Nwho was lured here by the fake letter,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.12,0:17:19.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and then he escaped suspicion\Nby having me vouch for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.59,0:17:21.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It really was quite impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.79,0:17:27.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You disappoint me. You're a lousy detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.00,0:17:31.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where is your proof that I killed her?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.50,0:17:36.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No court of law could make me stand trial like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.51,0:17:38.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's right, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.44,0:17:40.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I do have proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.74,0:17:45.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector. There's something I'd like you to get right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.22,0:17:49.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The tape of the phone call...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.89,0:17:51.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that all you need, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.96,0:17:54.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The tape of my wife on the phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.42,0:17:55.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you want with that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.79,0:17:58.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Play it, if you would.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.63,0:18:00.50,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.50,0:18:02.40,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Oh? You're not my husband...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.40,0:18:04.90,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Um, who may I ask is calling?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.90,0:18:08.97,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Who do you think? Mrs. Tatsumi, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.97,0:18:10.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.16,0:18:11.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A music box?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.07,0:18:12.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shh! Quiet!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.58,0:18:14.10,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Oops.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.11,0:18:18.25,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Little boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.25,0:18:19.82,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Could you put my husband on?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.82,0:18:22.12,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Yes, just a minute—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.12,0:18:23.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.25,0:18:27.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now do you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.26,0:18:32.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That hotel uses this music box in place of alarm clock buzzers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.60,0:18:35.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, your wife had set the alarm
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.53,0:18:39.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but forgot to turn it off when making the call.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.77,0:18:43.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, but music boxes like this can be found anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.21,0:18:45.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It doesn't prove a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.11,0:18:46.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.31,0:18:48.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Any music boxes where the body was found?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.44,0:18:51.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, none at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.05,0:18:55.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer could have run off with it for whatever reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.95,0:18:58.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unlikely.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.19,0:18:59.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And why's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.82,0:19:01.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan. The tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.99,0:19:04.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.16,0:19:05.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.03,0:19:10.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a recording of the music box in the room next to Mr. Tatsumi's office!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.24,0:19:15.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Give it a listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.11,0:19:24.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.31,0:19:26.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's missing a note!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.92,0:19:30.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. The music box in the next room over
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.65,0:19:37.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,is probably missing either a cylinder pin or a tooth!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.93,0:19:43.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, it's the only music box like it in the world, Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.67,0:19:49.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now then, let's hear the phone recording one more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.77,0:19:51.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would be a waste of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.88,0:19:59.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To think a lawyer would be blackmailed by his own wife...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.22,0:20:01.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Blackmailed? By your wife?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.75,0:20:04.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She demanded 200 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.05,0:20:05.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two hundred million?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.99,0:20:10.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It took skill to get where I am today.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.49,0:20:17.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But because of my position, I'm often privy to corporate secrets and the like.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.30,0:20:19.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I never made any demands,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.24,0:20:22.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but a lot of extra money was added to my counsel fees.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.57,0:20:26.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Some of it was illegal, to be more precise.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.14,0:20:28.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazumi found out about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.51,0:20:30.75,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I'll keep quiet if you give me 200 million—
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.75,0:20:35.62,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}a year's worth of this dirty money—\Nin the form of divorce compensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.62,0:20:39.69,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's not that much when you consider you can keep your reputation.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.69,0:20:44.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But then she got involved with that designer...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.46,0:20:46.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't let her get away with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.96,0:20:50.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I'll do what you want, but on one condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.17,0:20:54.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Call me at the specified time\Nor else I won't pay the 200 million!"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.54,0:20:58.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She agreed without a single question.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.14,0:21:00.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She would get 200 million and her man!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.68,0:21:02.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was only natural.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.55,0:21:05.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you shouldn't have made her call.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.98,0:21:08.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You had the call recorded automatically,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.08,0:21:11.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but you should've listened to it again\Nbefore giving it to the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.55,0:21:16.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your trick to pull off the perfect crime\Nactually wound up proving your guilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.89,0:21:21.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I gambled with myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.16,0:21:26.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter how good the lawyer,\Nthe moment of truth is always a gamble.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.70,0:21:31.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Until now, I'd never once lost that bet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.24,0:21:36.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You may be a good lawyer,\Nbut you were a poor criminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.01,0:21:38.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's how it is, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.99,0:23:25.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.99,0:23:28.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good work, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.19,0:23:30.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Despite being tricked and taken advantage of.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.46,0:23:32.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hope to work with you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.46,0:23:34.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, uh, same here...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.46,0:23:37.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tricked? Who? By who?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.20,0:23:38.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, well!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.87,0:23:40.24,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Gimme a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.24,0:23:43.57,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Now his reputation keeps getting better and better...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.75,0:23:52.15,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It was definitely Matsuo{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} who did this!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.15,0:23:56.85,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But how did he go from the studio\Nand back in four minutes?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.85,0:24:01.42,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Aha! I've finally found the secret path!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.42,0:24:04.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't want the criminal to leave
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.93,0:24:07.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when the logic show's just about to begin...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.93,0:24:10.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...Takashi Matsuo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.40,0:24:17.41,Signs,,0,0,0,,Next Conan:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.28,0:24:22.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint: Window
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.01,0:24:24.81,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,A new opening theme starts next time!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.81,0:24:27.42,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Really, really? I'm looking forward to it, super-very-good!
